<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,949,1115]" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">
The members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[388,499,949,976]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suffusa">
<emphasis box="[388,405,950,975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[420,499,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">suffusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group are pale coloured moths with distinct waved transversal lines, paleyellowish reniform and characteristic dark rounded subapical mark; in the male genitalia the saccus is V-like; the valva are asymmetrical and the ampullae asymmetrical or symmetrical; the yuxta forms circle, right valva larger or slightly smaller than left one, the aedeagus is incurved medially, not tapered towards the apex; the vesica bears a row of more than 5 small triangular cornuti.
</paragraph>
